{
  "doc_id": "45039",
  "text": "MATLAB [53] is a multiparadigm numerical computing environment and fourth-generation programming language. It can be used for accelerator modeling because numerous toolboxes of this system can provide the researcher with all necessary subprograms, including integration of equations of motion and space charge calculation. Due to its powerful graphical potential, MATLAB can be useful as a postprocessor for analysis of simulation results. So, it was logical that MATLAB was used as a platform for program complexes for cyclotron beam dynamics simulations, one of which was developed at JINR (Dubna, Russia) [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
